      • Cell

        public Cell(CellGrid grid,
            int row,
            int column)
        Constructs a new Cell that belongs to the specified grid and has a location indicated by the specified row and column arguments. More specifically, the row and column represent the Cell's location within the full grid rather than the visible grid.
        Parameters:
        grid - the CellGrid this Cell belongs to
        row - the row location of this Cell within the full grid
        column - the column location of this Cell within the full grid

      • setVisible

        public void setVisible(boolean visible)
        Sets the visible state of this Cell to the provided boolean argument. If the visible argument is true then this Cell should be within the visible grid. If the visible argument is false then this Cell should not be within the visible grid.
        Parameters:
        visible - the boolean value to set this Cell's visible state to

      • visible
